{"word":"H5062 - נָגַף - nâgaph - naw-gaf' - Beat","slug":"H5062","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">נָגַף</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>nâgaph"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>naw-gaf'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Beat"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05E0;&#x05D2;&#x05E3; - na&#x0302;gaph</b> - <i>naw-gaf'</i><p/>A primitive root; to <i>push</i>, <i>gore</i>, <i>defeat</i>, <i>stub</i> (the toe), <i>inflict</i> (a disease): - beat, dash, hurt, plague, slay, smite (down), strike, stumble, X surely, put to the worse."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H4046\">H4046</a>, <a href=\"#/H5063\">H5063</a>"}]}